*********************************
***** PY_HDF_READER LIBRARY *****
*********************************

0 - Informations :
------------------
Version : 0.0.0
Author(s) : CGTD/UDEV/N. PASCAL
Plateform : linux

1 - Description :
-----------------
Python library for reading the HDF4 files

2 - Package Content :
---------------------

<installation_directory>
           |
           |-doc/
           |  |-html/    the API documentation
           |
           |-src/        the library sources (*.py)
           |
           |-example/    the sources of basic usage examples. See here for a quick example of main useful routines
           |             like : reading a sds data, reading an attribute, obtaining informations about an HDF file...
           |
           |-data/       an example of HDF4 file use by the example sources

3 - Prerequisites :
-------------------------
HDF4 library >=4.2r1   (http://hdf.ncsa.uiuc.edu/products/hdf4/index.html)
pyhdf        >=0.7-3   (http://pysclint.sourceforge.net/pyhdf/)
numpy        >= 1.0.0  (http://numpy.scipy.org/)

4 - Utilisation :
-----------------
Use it as a classic python library

(1) Add <installation_directory>/src to your PYTHONPATH environment variable. If you do not have one already set, create it. And of course, replace <installation_directory> with the path of the package extraction directory.

    For example, if you are using a bash interpreter, you can add to your $HOME/.bash_profile the line :
        export PYTHONPATH=<installation_directory>/src:$PYTHONPATH
    And then type
        source $HOME/.bash_profile

(2) Add to the imports of your python scripts (see the example/test_py_hdf_reader.py file if it does not make sense for you)
        from py_hdf_reader import *

